# Combinational Circuits in Verilog HDL

This folder contains my implementation of fundamental combinational logic circuits using **Verilog HDL**. These projects are part of my journey toward becoming an **RTL Design / ASIC Design Engineer**.

The objective of this folder is to understand how digital logic is translated into hardware using Verilog, learn RTL coding practices, write testbenches, simulate designs, and verify functionality using waveform analysis.

---

## Learning Objectives

Through these projects, I learned:

- Fundamentals of combinational logic design
- Gate-level modelling using built-in Verilog primitives
- Module declaration and port definition
- Module instantiation
- Structural design methodology
- Writing synthesizable Verilog code
- Creating Verilog testbenches
- Applying different input test cases
- Using `$monitor`, `$dumpfile`, and `$dumpvars`
- Generating VCD (Value Change Dump) files
- Verifying outputs using GTKWave
- Basic Verilog simulation flow using Icarus Verilog

---

